hotelname: Capri by Fraser China Square, Singapore
review_pos: The location was excellent to explore Singa on foot and the hotel was very new. The pool and gym had superb views and the room had everything one needed including unlimited drinking water from a filtered tap.
review_neg: Room was on the small side but that is to be expected in Singapore, also quite pricey like everything in Singa.
review_text: The location was excellent to explore Singa on foot and the hotel was very new. The pool and gym had superb views and the room had everything one needed including unlimited drinking water from a filtered tap. Room was on the small side but that is to be expected in Singapore, also quite pricey like everything in Singa.

hotelname: Capri by Fraser China Square, Singapore
review_pos: I like the hotel location and of course the room itself.It quite small compared to the price but hey its Singapore hence the room not as wide as the price  is!The room is super clean and new! review_neg: I don't like the breakfast at all! With the price that we paid i think we are deserved to have a breakfast like a champion! The food is so basic and not so much on the varieties. The food is tasteless. Should have more type of food and can be cook better.

review_pos: Staff, location, cleanliness, amenities.The amenities, especially the location is excellent but it was the staff that really made our stay exceptional! hotelname: Capri by Fraser China Square, Singapore
review_pos: Room was very comfortable, decorated really nicely. Concierges are super charming and helpful. The location is great, within ~10 minutes' walk from at least seven hawker centres!
review_neg: I hate the current trend for hotel rooms having glass doors for the toilets. And the sink is in the room, no walls, so if you use the sink or bathroom light in the night, whoever else is in the room gets disturbed by it. Let bathrooms have actual walls, PLEASE!
review_text: Room was very comfortable, decorated really nicely. Concierges are super charming and helpful. The location is great, within ~10 minutes' walk from at least seven hawker centres! I hate the current trend for hotel rooms having glass doors for the toilets. And the sink is in the room, no walls, so if you use the sink or bathroom light in the night, whoever else is in the room gets disturbed by it. Let bathrooms have actual walls, PLEASE!

hotelname: Capri by Fraser China Square, Singapore
review_pos: Central location, 5 minutes walk from the Chinatown and Telok Ayer MRT stations, very convenient for a first time visitor wanting to explore different parts of the city state. Sentosa Express and Cable cars are 2 MRT stations away, and Changi Airport is 30 minutes by taxi.The pool on the roof is great, and not crowded.
review_neg: I specifically indicated that there were three of us, including a 8-year old child. In Europe and America for such bookings I always got a room with an extra bed ( a cot or a folding armchair) without a special request. Here you get a room with a standard double bed for the three of us. And the room's layout does not really allow to put even a small extra bed, which is why we did not bother to ask for one. We decided it was OK for the 6 nights, though it would have been a lot better to have a separate bed for our daughter.
review_text: Central location, 5 minutes walk from the Chinatown and Telok Ayer MRT stations, very convenient for a first time visitor wanting to explore different parts of the city state. We decided it was OK for the 6 nights, though it would have been a lot better to have a separate bed for our daughter.
